<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_86ec44a5-50e5-46af-a9b2-690f1763ff9b" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/></meta><sptc>H3V4</sptc><title id="_ff90c3c7-f61e-4e39-b532-6c6aa9bd89e5">Avoidance of spread of fire between Class 2-9 buildings</title><archive-num>2019: V2.3.1.4</archive-num><subclause id="_5ff42b98-dec6-4d9f-a85d-39a34daffac7" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_3cb710a7-9711-4eae-8ab7-ca7e3407991d">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Compliance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1869_0.14.0.xml#_9d47c3bf-6a3c-4c83-ad7a-1a018d707131" id="_cf92b1e2-7094-4508-a0a4-711bbbef1425" scope="local" type="subclause">H3P1(2)</xref> to avoid a Class 10a building increasing the risk of fire spread between Class 2-9 buildings is verified when it is calculated that a building—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_a5a126cf-fe2d-42bb-836d-2b957367d2de">is capable of withstanding the heat flux set out in column 2 of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/135_0.4.0.xml#_5103a71c-d49d-4110-bf59-db5ab321f013" id="_d9792aac-d937-4056-b5cd-eedebbacabfc" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table H3V4</xref> without ignition; and</li><li id="_24739e63-3dbe-4ba2-bf22-19befeb91005">will not cause heat flux in excess of those set out in column 2 of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/135_0.4.0.xml#_5103a71c-d49d-4110-bf59-db5ab321f013" id="_58822a8a-6c33-4ed0-9139-3c91e747ddea" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table H3V4</xref>, when the distance between the buildings is as set out in column 1 of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/135_0.4.0.xml#_5103a71c-d49d-4110-bf59-db5ab321f013" id="_a30b6015-cd33-41ef-b525-5c409d00b149" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="table-reference">Table H3V4</xref>.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_12b16bef-23f8-4393-8821-abbbfd4fecd6"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>H3V4 is equivalent to <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1788#_c3fe2c22-c61d-4669-9b88-4f55bb3d7385" id="_97ca3364-9013-4e5c-b562-004d7b09dfa0" publishing-id="vol1" scope="external" type="clause">C1V2</xref> in NCC Volume One. Guidance on the use of <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1788#_c3fe2c22-c61d-4669-9b88-4f55bb3d7385" id="_5a76dc32-93fb-4da1-9b84-bcfcc6fabe7b" publishing-id="vol1" scope="external" type="clause">C1V2</xref> can be found in the Guide to NCC Volume One, and is applicable to the use of H3V4.</p></callout><table-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/135_0.4.0.xml" graph="None" id="_5103a71c-d49d-4110-bf59-db5ab321f013"><num/><title id="_9f4d1238-511a-4694-bf6e-50867c2cbd49"/></table-reference></clause>